{"image": "http://giottojs.org/media/giottoweb/giotto.png", "site": {"year": 2014, "python_version": "3.4.2", "url": "http://giottojs.org", "template": "partials/base.html", "media": "/media", "date": "2014-12-18T12-05-15", "lux_version": "0.1.2-alpha.1", "name": "Lux", "template_engine": null}, "modified": "2014-12-17T15:48:06", "slug": "api/chart", "title": "GiottoJS - Chart API", "content_type": "text/html", "name": "api_chart", "head": {"twitter:card": "summary_large_image", "title": "GiottoJS - Chart API"}, "html_url": "http://giottojs.org/api/chart", "html": {"main": "<div id=\"page-main\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"page-header\">\n<h2>GiottoJS - Chart API</h2>\n</div>\n<div data-highlight>\n<p>Charts have the same base api as all <a href=\"http://giottojs.org/api/visualization\">visualizations</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"chartaddseries\"># chart.addSeries(series)</h3>\n<p>Add additional data series to the chart. The chart is not rendered, call\n<a href=\"http://giottojs.org/api/visualization\">render</a> to draw the series.</p>\n<p>Redraw the chart</p>\n<h3 id=\"chartdraw\"># chart.draw()</h3>\n<p>Redraw the chart</p>\n<h2 id=\"options\">Options</h2>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"footer\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 small\">\n<p>Library released under the <a href=\"http://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-3-Clause\">BSD License</a>.</p>\n<p>Copyright 2014 <a href=\"http://lucasbardella.com\">Luca Sbardella</a> and <a href=\"http://quantmind.com\">Quantmind</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>"}, "api_url": "http://giottojs.org/ng/site/api/chart.json"}